Defendant Nicholas D Longo in court, in custody, with attorney Kelsey Morin.   Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to Count #4.  Court finds the defendant guilty of Count #4.  Counts 1,2 and 3 are dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Morin makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Victim makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following:
Count #4
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
6 months Huber concurrent (Credit - 30 days if revoked) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.

Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Maintain/Obtain part time employment;
No violent contact with victim S. L.
No possession of weapons.
Obtain H.S. Diploma.  
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge
Costs: $343.00 to be paid as a condition of probation.  
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation. 
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
